İ.B.B (Istanbul metropolitan municipality) Istanbul Waste Incineration and Energy Production Facility (Fig. 18.5
                     ) is Europe’s biggest waste incineration and energy production facility, with a daily capacity of 3000 tons and an annual capacity of 

                     approximately 1 million tons. The facility eliminates 15% of Istanbul’s day-to-day household waste, meets the electricity requirements of nearly 1.4 million people with the 85MW of electricity it produces, and prevents the release of 1.38 million tons of greenhouse gas emissions into the atmosphere annually. Organic wastes are processed and converted into electrical energy in a biomethanization facility. This facility will produce biogas from organic wastes in an oxygen-free environment. The obtained biogas generates electrical energy with an installed power of 1.4MW (Energy from Waste, 2023).
